commit.message:
Use importlib.reload instead of imp.reload

The imp module has been deprecated since Python 3.4 and is removed in
Python 3.12.
Replace its use with its replacement in the importlib module.

Signed-off-by: David Runge <dave@sleepmap.de>
std::allocator's construct and destroy -> std::allocator_traits (issue #532)
multi_handle.hxx: enable two forward decls also for Visual Studio (issue #533)
Allow users to overwrite CMAKE_CXX_STANDARD

Enforce using C++11

Support for older standards was dropped in #507

Keeping the default CMAKE_CXX_EXTENSIONS=ON fixes #550
random_shuffle removed in c++17

Remove pragma from config.hxx

Closes https://github.com/ukoethe/vigra/issues/482

commit.message: python linking workaround on OSX only in conda-based builds
change order to find packages

specify zlib/png directly

also use correct extension for osx/lnx

Skip linking to `libpython` on macOS

The interpreter is statically linked to `libpython` on macOS. Likely
causes symbol clashes, which causes the segmentation faults we have
seen.

See also https://github.com/conda-forge/vigra-feedstock/blob/34e1048c818424995997b59817bbf909f43b221b/recipe/patches/ignore_libpython_macos.diff

Co-authored-by: John Kirkham <jakirkham@users.noreply.github.com>

run osx tests in ci, add shebang to test scripts

otherwise they won't run on osx
for C++20 (and beyond), don't refer to std::unary_negate or std::binary_negate (#534)
